
1) Easiest- clone linux-64 environment:
$ conda install --name ELT-2-ChIP --file ELT-2-ChIP.env.linux-64.txt
$ conda activate ELT-2-ChIP

2) Install conda packages manually:
# put samtools in the create step because of an issue with openssl (https://github.com/bioconda/bioconda-recipes/issues/13958)
$ conda create --name ELT-2-ChIP python=3.7 r-base=4.0 samtools -c bioconda
$ conda activate ELT-2-ChIP
$ conda install -c anaconda openjdk
$ conda install r-spp idr bedtools bwa deeptools ucsc-bedgraphtobigwig ucsc-wigtobigwig bx-python meme -c bioconda
# the following are for the R part of the pipeline
$ conda install r-stringr r-reshape2 r-rcolorbrewer r-ggextra r-venndiagram r-dplyr r-pheatmap r-knitr r-ggplot2 r-upsetr
$ conda install bioconductor-ChIPpeakAnno bioconductor-topGO bioconductor-plyranges bioconductor-biomart -c bioconda

Notes:

SPP:
It is an R package, but the authors have written a wrapper script: run_spp.R from https://github.com/kundajelab/phantompeakqualtools

java:
conda install -c anaconda openjdk
